  "type": "Example",
  "number": "1.2.17",
  "title": "",
  "body": " Suppose we are converting temperature from Fahrenheit to Celsius based on a thermometer reading. The formula is . The 32 and 5\/9 are exact numbers (part of the definition of the Fahrenheit and Celsius systems).  If we read the temperature as 44.7 F then the conversion is as follows. In the subtraction step the 32 is exact so the precision is determined by solely 44.7 (tenths place). In the multipication step the 5\/9 is exact so the precision is determined by the 12.7 (three significant digits).  "
