  "body": "  As the angle of bank increases (from 0 to 60 ) what happens to the stall speed?    If we look in the Up row, the stall speed changes from 48 to 52 to 57 to 68. The first thing we notice is that the stall speed increases.  If we repeat this in the Approach row, we again see the speeds are increasing. The same is true in the Landing row.  Thus we can say that stall speed increases as the angle of bank increases.  In later sections ( ) we will learn to be more specific about patterns when possible.   "
